    hide mara_kestrel

    scene bg ch15_3be532_3 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A wind that sounds like memory]
    "There is no neat justice in the aftermath. There is only repair work and accounting and the slow, difficult labor of living with consequences. Livia Chen's legal maneuvers will shape the next months; council seats will"
    "change hands; people will leave. You will be called brave, foolish, responsible, naive. All of it will be true and none will carry the single answer the town needs."
    "You and Eli stay on the rooftop long after the town's lights blink off. Your hands are folded together. The storm has taken some things and left others, and whatever future you hold will be braided with the storm's tally."
    "You are tired to the bone. You are angry down to the marrow. You are standing inside a love that is not cure but recognition—two people who saw a town break and tried, imperfectly, to hold it together. That, for now, must be enough."

